  }, `Despite the obvious respect he garnered from the press—and the markers of more mainstream white stardom, such as riding in the prestigious motor coach frequented by powerful white Hollywood stars and executives, he faced the usual marginalization for people of color in Hollywood. Jack Carter was the lowest paid actor of the cast, with an intended salary of \$200 a week (Richard Wilson - Orson Welles Papers). The Dunbar Hotel was also far away from many of the other actors who were living or lodging near Beverly Hills (Richard Wilson - Orson Welles Papers). `), React.createElement(MDXTag, {
