  }, `However, the history of the Dunbar Hotel suggests that Carter may have found a sense of community while living in Los Angeles and was certainly warmly welcomed there. However, his activities weren’t covered in the press or archival material, so little is known about the details of Carter’s stay at the Dunbar. However, at least inadvertently, Welles’s casting choice integrated Carter into a rich cultural center for African Americans during the time period. `), React.createElement(MDXTag, {
